cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a deep learning architecture for hyperspectral image classification, which involves image processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also addresses the challenges of high dimensionality and limited labelled data, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of spectral partitioning and convolutional neural networks also indicates that it could be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
